description: From Latin etesius (“annual”), from Ancient Greek ἐτήσιος (etḗsios, “annual”), from ἔτος (étos, “year”).

entries.meaning: Pertaining to a dry north wind which blows in the eastern Mediterranean.
examples: Is it from those etesian winds, or melting of snow in the mountains under the Equator […], or from those great dropping perpetual showers […]?

entries.meaning: A dry north wind which blows in the eastern Mediterranean.
